# VLAN Configuration Plan

## Planned VLANs

| VLAN | Name |
|------:|------|
| 10 | MANAGEMENT |
| 20 | ICT |
| 30 | HR |
| 40 | FINANCE |
| 50 | SALES |
| 60 | SUPPORT |
| 70 | SERVERS |
| 80 | CCTV |
| 90 | PRINTERS |
| 100 | GUEST_WIFI |
| 110 | NETWORK_MANAGEMENT |

---

## Inter-VLAN Routing

Routing will be performed by the Cisco Catalyst 9500 Layer 3 Core Switch.

---

## Trunk Links

802.1Q trunking will be configured between:

- Core Switch ↔ Distribution Switches
- Distribution Switches ↔ Access Switches

---

## Access Ports

End devices will be assigned to their respective departmental VLANs.

---

## Native VLAN

VLAN 999 will be reserved as the native VLAN for trunk links.

---

## Management VLAN

VLAN 110 will be used exclusively for switch management and administrative access.
